IMPORTANT:
- The "findings" array MUST be empty if no fund-theft vulnerability exists. Zero findings is a valid and expected output.
- Every finding MUST have severity "Critical". If it is not Critical, do not include it.
- Every finding MUST describe a concrete attack by an unprivileged third party that results in loss of funds.
- Confidence MUST be 0.8 or higher. If you are less confident, do not include the finding.
- Do NOT include findings about admin abuse, gas optimization, code quality, centralization risk, or denial of service.

Only output the JSON object, no additional text or markdown formatting.
